For Function 8, Week 4's strategy (Automatic Relevance Determination (ARD) applied to the RBF kernel with conservative baseline (length_scale=[1.0]*8) and wider 
bounds (length_scale_bounds=(1e-6, 1e8)), Sobol sampling and Thompson sampling) has yielded an output (9.8699663885489) which is extremely similar to the outputs 
of all the other 3 queries that have been previously submitted (Week 1: 9.8658669584059, Week 2: 9.9561276549796, Week 3: 9.8938255194366). This strengthtens the 
hypothesis that the global maximum might have already been identified in Week 2 and this overall identified area of Black-Box Function 8 does not just represent a 
local maximum, because using both the UCB acquisition function with a balance between exploration and exploitation (Weeks 1-3) and Thompson sampling (Week 4) with 
Automatic Relevance Determination (ARD) applied on the RBF kernel pointed towards the same area with overall maximised outputs.
